Sure, I'll provide you with a simple example of a PHP code for a basic calculator that can perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. This example involves a form where a user can input two numbers and select an operation to perform. After submitting the form, the PHP script will process the input and display the result.

Here's the code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Simple PHP Calculator</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Simple Calculator in PHP</h2>
<form method="post">
    <input type="text" name="number1" id="number1" placeholder="Enter number 1" required>
    <input type="text" name="number2" id="number2" placeholder="Enter number 2" required>

    <select name="operation">
        <option value="add">Add</option>
        <option value="subtract">Subtract</option>
        <option value="multiply">Multiply</option>
        <option value="divide">Divide</option>
    </select>

    <button type="submit" name="calculate">Calculate</button>
</form>

<?php
if (isset($_POST['calculate'])) {
    $number1 = $_POST['number1'];
    $number2 = $_POST['number2'];
    $operation = $_POST['operation'];
    $result = 0;

    switch ($operation) {
        case 'add':
            $result = $number1 + $number2;
            break;
        case 'subtract':
            $result = $number1 - $number2;
            break;
        case 'multiply':
            $result = $number1 * $number2;
            break;
        case 'divide':
            if ($number2 == 0) {
                echo "Division by zero is not allowed.";
                return;
            }
            $result = $number1 / $number2;
            break;
    }

    echo "Result: " . $result;
}
?>

</body>
</html>
```

- This HTML form (`<form>...</form>`) allows users to input two numbers and select an operation (add, subtract, multiply, divide) from a dropdown menu.
- When the form is submitted, the PHP script runs (`if (isset($_POST['calculate'])) {...}`) processing the two numbers and the selected operation.
- Depending on the operation chosen, the respective case is executed within the switch statement.
- The result of the calculation is then displayed on the page (`echo "Result: " . $result;`).

Remember to use this code within a PHP capable server environment. You could run this on a local server like XAMPP or a live server that supports PHP.
